.\" pmemtester - Parallel wrapper for memtester
.\" SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
.TH PMEMTESTER 1 "2026-03-06" "pmemtester 0.7" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pmemtester \- parallel memory testing with EDAC hardware error detection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pmemtester
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pmemtester
is a parallel wrapper for
.BR memtester (8)
that runs multiple memtester instances simultaneously (one per physical CPU
core), divides RAM equally among them, and validates results using both
memtester exit codes and Linux EDAC (Error Detection and Correction) hardware
error counters.
.PP
Testing proceeds in two phases:
.TP
.B Phase 1 (memtester)
Deterministic memory test patterns run in parallel across all cores.
.TP
.B Phase 2 (stressapptest)
Optional randomised bus-contention stress test using Google's stressapptest.
Runs only if the binary is found (or forced with \fB\-\-stressapptest on\fR).
.PP
EDAC counters are compared before, between, and after test phases to detect
hardware-reported ECC errors that may not manifest as memtester failures.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-percent " N"
Percentage of RAM to test (0.001\-100, default: 90). Supports up to 3
decimal places (e.g., 0.1 for a quick smoke test).
.TP
.BI \-\-size " SIZE"
Total RAM to test with a unit suffix: K (KiB), M (MiB), G (GiB), T (TiB).
For example, \fB\-\-size 256M\fR tests 256 MiB. Mutually exclusive with
\fB\-\-percent\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-ram\-type " TYPE"
RAM measurement basis: \fBavailable\fR (default), \fBtotal\fR, or \fBfree\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-memtester\-dir " DIR"
Directory containing the memtester binary (default: /usr/local/bin).
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-dir " DIR"
Directory for log files (default: /tmp/pmemtester.PID).
.TP
.BI \-\-iterations " N"
Number of memtester iterations per thread (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-ce
Allow correctable EDAC errors (CE); only fail on uncorrectable errors (UE).
Without this flag, any EDAC error (CE or UE) causes a FAIL verdict.
.TP
.BI \-\-color " MODE"
Coloured terminal output: \fBauto\fR (default), \fBon\fR, or \fBoff\fR.
Auto mode detects terminal capability and honours the \fBNO_COLOR\fR
environment variable.
.TP
.BI \-\-stressapptest " MODE"
Control the stressapptest pass: \fBauto\fR (default, runs if binary found and
Phase 1 passed), \fBon\fR (mandatory, fails if binary absent), or \fBoff\fR
(disabled).
.TP
.BI \-\-stressapptest\-seconds " N"
Stressapptest duration in seconds. 0 (default) matches the Phase 1
wall-clock time.
.TP
.BI \-\-stressapptest\-dir " DIR"
Directory containing the stressapptest binary (default: /usr/local/bin).
.TP
.BI \-\-estimate " MODE"
Time estimation calibration: \fBauto\fR (default, silently skips on failure),
\fBon\fR (warns on failure), or \fBoff\fR (skips entirely).
.TP
.B \-\-stop\-on\-error
Stop immediately when any error is detected (memtester exit or EDAC
uncorrectable error). Remaining memtester instances are killed, and Phase 2
is skipped.
.TP
.BI \-\-threads " N"
Number of memtester instances to run (default: auto-detect physical cores
via lscpu). Warns if N exceeds the logical CPU count.
.TP
.BI \-\-numa\-node " N"
Constrain testing to NUMA node N, or comma-separated nodes (e.g., 0,1,2)
for parallel multi-node testing. Each memtester instance and stressapptest
are wrapped with \fBnumactl \-\-cpunodebind=N \-\-membind=N\fR. The core
count is automatically set to the number of physical cores on that node.
For multi-node, each node runs its own pipeline in parallel with per-node
results. CPU-less nodes automatically borrow CPUs from a donor node.
Requires \fBnumactl\fR to be installed. In single-node mode, CPU-less
NUMA nodes (e.g., HBM) produce an error with a workaround suggestion.
.TP
.B \-\-pin
Pin each memtester instance to a specific physical CPU core using
\fBtaskset\fR. Uses \fBlscpu \-b \-p=Socket,Core,CPU,Node\fR to map
physical cores to logical CPU IDs (lowest ID per core). Stressapptest
is also pinned. Eliminates scheduler migration for reproducible results.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-physical
Show virtual-to-physical address mapping for each memtester thread by
reading \fI/proc/PID/pagemap\fR. Reports the physical address range per
thread and, when EDAC errors are present, correlates them with memory
controller error addresses from dmesg. Requires root or
\fBCAP_SYS_ADMIN\fR (restricted since kernel 4.0). If the pagemap is not
readable, a warning is printed and testing continues normally.
.TP
.B \-\-check\-deps
Check all required and optional dependencies, display versions, paths,
and system capabilities, then exit. Returns 0 if all required dependencies
are found, 1 otherwise.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show usage summary and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All tests passed and no EDAC errors detected (or CE only with \fB\-\-allow\-ce\fR).
.TP
.B 1
One or more tests failed, or EDAC errors were detected, or a required
dependency is missing (with \fB\-\-check\-deps\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
Test 90% of available RAM (default):
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester
.RE
.fi
.PP
Test 80% of total RAM with 3 iterations:
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-percent 80 \-\-ram\-type total \-\-iterations 3
.RE
.fi
.PP
Test exactly 256 MiB:
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-size 256M
.RE
.fi
.PP
Test NUMA node 0 with CPU pinning:
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-numa\-node 0 \-\-pin \-\-percent 90
.RE
.fi
.PP
Test multiple NUMA nodes in parallel:
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-numa\-node 0,1 \-\-percent 90
.RE
.fi
.PP
Quick smoke test (0.1% of RAM):
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-percent 0.1
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check dependencies before running:
.PP
.nf
.RS
sudo pmemtester \-\-check\-deps
.RE
.fi
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.SS Required
.TP
.B memtester
Memory testing tool (not bundled). See \fIhttps://pyropus.ca./software/memtester/\fR.
.TP
.B lscpu
CPU topology detection (from util-linux).
.TP
.B awk\fR, \fBfind\fR, \fBdiff
Standard Unix utilities used for text processing and EDAC comparison.
.SS Optional
.TP
.B stressapptest
Randomised stress testing tool by Google. Auto mode silently skips if
absent. See \fIhttps://github.com/stressapptest/stressapptest\fR.
.TP
.B numactl
Required only for \fB\-\-numa\-node\fR.
.TP
.B taskset
Required only for \fB\-\-pin\fR (from util-linux).
.TP
.B dmesg
Used for EDAC message capture.
.TP
.B nproc
Fallback for core count detection if lscpu fails.
.TP
.B od
Binary file reader (from coreutils). Required only for \fB\-\-show\-physical\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /proc/meminfo
System memory information.
.TP
.I /sys/devices/system/edac/mc/
EDAC memory controller sysfs directory. Absent on systems without ECC RAM
or without an EDAC driver loaded.
.TP
.I /proc/PID/pagemap
Per-process virtual-to-physical page mapping. Used by \fB\-\-show\-physical\fR.
Requires root or \fBCAP_SYS_ADMIN\fR.
.TP
.I /sys/devices/system/node/
NUMA node sysfs directory.
.TP
.I /tmp/pmemtester.PID/
Default log directory (override with \fB\-\-log\-dir\fR). Contains per-thread
logs (\fIthread_N.log\fR), a master log (\fImaster.log\fR), and EDAC
snapshots.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR memtester (8),
.BR stressapptest (1),
.BR numactl (8),
.BR taskset (1),
.BR lscpu (1),
.BR edac\-util (8)
